Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at a private residence in New Orleans, Louisiana. She praised Congressman Cedric Richmond for his leadership and influence in Congress, as well as his role in the campaign that elected President Joe Biden and herself. Harris also thanked the hosts of the event and acknowledged the presence of other political leaders in attendance. She highlighted the accomplishments of the Biden administration, such as capping the cost of insulin for seniors, negotiating drug prices, investing in infrastructure, and reducing child poverty. Harris expressed concern about recent Supreme Court decisions and the attacks on voting rights and women's reproductive rights. She emphasized the importance of fighting for freedom, equality, and justice, both in the United States and on the global stage. Harris urged the audience to continue the fight for democracy and to protect the values that define America.